===Etymology 2===
{{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/mə/}} → {{IPAchar|/mo/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*mə}}. Appears in common use in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' (712 {{CE}}), with the only attested distinction between {{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>1</sub>⟩}} and {{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>2</sub>⟩}}. Compare {{cog|ltc|-}} {{ltc-l|母}}.

Distinct from {{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>1</sub>⟩}} terms such as {{m|ja|雲|tr={{IPAfont|⟨kumo<sub>1</sub>⟩}} → kumo||[[cloud]]}} and {{m|ja|下|tr={{IPAfont|⟨simo<sub>1</sub>⟩}} → shimo||[[lower]], [[end]]}}; pronounced closely to {{cog|ltc|-}} {{ltc-l|毛}}.

This distinction was lost in a later ancient Japanese chronicle, the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' (720 {{CE}}), and {{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>1</sub>⟩}} and {{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>2</sub>⟩}} were merged to form one syllable ''mo''. See the {{w|Man'yōgana}} and {{w|Jōdai Tokushu Kanazukai}} articles for more detail on ancient spellings.

